<topic title="Keyboard mapping">
  <style>
    .keyboard {
    text-align: center;
    margin: 24pt;
    }
    
    .keyboard-title {
    font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .keyboard table {
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    }

    .keyboard th,td {
    text-align: left;
    }
    
    .keyboard th {
    background: #cfc;
    }

    .keyboard td {
    background: #eee;
    }
  </style>

  <h2>Atari Keys</h2>

  <p>
    When possible, Atari keys are mapped to the host keys that generate the same characters. For instance, Shift+2 on a US English keyboard layout
    generates an @ key press in the emulated system, even though Shift+2 generates a double quote (") on the Atari keyboard. Here are the less
    obvious mappings:
  </p>
  
  <div class="keyboard">
    <table>
      <tr>
        <th>Atari key</th>
        <th>Host key</th>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Start</td>
        <td>F2</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Select</td>
        <td>F3</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Option</td>
        <td>F4</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>System Reset (Warm Reset)</td>
        <td>F5</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Power (Cold Reset)</td>
        <td>Shift+F5</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Help</td>
        <td>F6</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Break</td>
        <td>F7/Pause</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+&lt; (Clear)</td>
        <td>Home</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+&gt; (Insert Line)</td>
        <td>Shift+Insert</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+&gt; (Insert Character)</td>
        <td>Insert</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Shift+Backspace (Delete Line)</td>
        <td>Shift+Delete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Backspace (Delete Character)</td>
        <td>Delete</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Fuji / Invert</td>
        <td>End or `</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Esc</td>
        <td>Ctrl+\</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+Esc</td>
        <td>Ctrl+Shift+\</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+-</td>
        <td>Up Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+=</td>
        <td>Down Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl++</td>
        <td>Left Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Ctrl+*</td>
        <td>Right Arrow*</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
  </div>
  <ul>
    <li>
      The Options / Keyboard... dialog allows configuration of the arrow key handling and can be set to either
      require or not require use of the Ctrl modifier key. Also, holding the Alt key will allow the arrow keys
      on the host to issue keyboard input even if those keys are already mapped to an input controller.
    </li>
  </ul>

